description: 'Shrinkflation' labels should be added to products to shame companies which reduce the size of their goods but charge customers the same, a think tank has suggested.
title: Shrinkflation: Customers should be warned by manufacturers when they reduce the size of products with labels detailing how much has been lopped off, think tank tells Rachel Reeves
